## Getting Started
To get a local copy up and running, follow these simple steps:

### Prerequisites
- [Git](https://git-scm.com/)
- Web browser (e.g., Chrome, Firefox)

### Installation
1. Clone the repository:
    ```bash
    git clone https://github.com/your-username/alx_html_css.git
    ```

2. Navigate to the project directory:
    ```bash
    cd alx_html_css
    ```

3. Open the `index.html` file in your browser to view the project:
    ```bash
    open css_basic/index.html
    ```

## Usage
- The `css_basic` directory contains basic HTML and CSS files demonstrating foundational concepts.
- The `css_advanced` directory contains more advanced CSS styling techniques.

## Features
- Responsive design using CSS Flexbox and Grid.
- Modern and clean UI design.
- Best practices for HTML and CSS structure.

